  {
    "Id": "870054",
    "ThreadId": "362345",
    "Html": "<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>Based on my understanding, this behavior is caused by the way you are defining the resources in your application. As mentioned in this related <a href=\"http://forums.silverlight.net/t/97612.aspx/1\">thread</a>, the search for a defined resource starts by crawling from the root of the <strong>ResouceDictionary </strong>and not from the first root, for example in your case the search will start from the <strong>ResourceDictionary </strong>containing the Style. Hence, in order to avoid this, for example you could try defining this resources at the same level.</p>\r\n<p>Also, take into account that as this may not be strictly related to <strong>Prism</strong>, I believe you could find better support about this subject for example in the <a href=\"http://forums.silverlight.net/\">Silverlight forums</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n<p>Agustin Adami<a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/aadami\"><br /> http://blogs.southworks.net/aadami</a></p>",
    "PostedDate": "2012-07-16T12:20:51.71-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
