    "Html": "<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>Based on my understanding, the problem is that you cannot add a <strong>ResourceDictionary </strong>inside another <strong>ResourceDictionary</strong>; you have to merge them inside the <strong>MergeDictionaries </strong>tag. The code-snippet posted by <strong>Agustin Adami</strong> is not meant to add entire <strong>ResourceDictionaries </strong>but resources directly (that is, the contents of the <strong>ResourceDictionaries</strong>) and therefore, you will need to add all styles / templates directly in the <strong>Application ResourceDictionary</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>However, as discussed previously, this is a limitation in <strong>Silverlight </strong>and is not related to <strong>Prism</strong>. Therefore, you might find better support for this in the <strong>Silverlight</strong> forums:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://forums.silverlight.net/\">Silverlight Forums</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n<p>Damian Cherubini<br /> <a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dcherubini\">http://blogs.southworks.net/dcherubini</a></p>",
